en_9252649_0	COLOMBO (News 1st) – The Presidential Commission to inquire into alleged irregularities at state institutions during the past four years has decided to investigate on a complaint against Minister Lakshman Kiriella.
en_9252649_1	The commission stated that the file containing information on the complaint was forwarded to the police in order to initiate the preliminary tasks.
en_9252649_2	The complaint was lodged by the Planters Association of Ceylon.
en_9252649_3	The complaint states that the Minister had unlawfully provided his wife, daughter, and relatives with land areas of 50,20 and 10 acres in Hantana belonging to the Janatha Estate Development Board.
en_9252649_4	Meanwhile, the commission stated that another complaint on alleged financial misappropriation worth billions of rupees that occurred when cancer medication was bought by the State Pharmaceutical Corporation.
en_9252649_5	This complaint was lodged by the Sri Lanka Chamber of Small and Medium Industries.
en_9252649_6	The commission has selected 07 complaints for investigation. Two hundred and ninety-five (295) complaints have been lodged with the commission.
en_9252649_7	Complaints will be accepted at the commission till March 7th.
